        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 6 at 2:57AM CDT until May 6 at 3:30AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 257 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles southwest of
Vancourt, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Vancourt around 300 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for west central
Texas.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
